Bayede Mobile will be available to a limited number of rural communities in KwaZulu-Natal. Courtesy #DStv403 NONGOMA - Zulu King Goodwill Zwelithini is planning to launch a new mobile network in South Africa next month. Bayede Mobile will be available to a limited number of rural communities in KwaZulu-Natal. The network will leverage existing infrastructure of some of South Africa’s biggest mobile networks. READ: King Zwelithini calls for inclusion of traditional leaders The Bayede Group says it will bring reliable connectivity at an affordable flat rate. King Zwelithini is partnering with the founders of JR Capital, and a well-established Mobile Virtual Network Enabler.